Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> In the latest commits of SilentDragon/hush I have gotten rid of all requirements to download any files (from centralized websites run by Zcash) before syncing a full node! Infinite % more bandwidth efficient than all other Zcash Protocol coins now. So with the next release of SilentDragon, you will be able to download a binary zip file and then just start syncing directly. No weird errors about missing params, no downloading huge big files. This also greatly improves censorship-resistance.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> Additionally this builds us closer so integrating into TAIL, to Tor operating system, since bandwidth is precious and Hush will need less bandwidth than any other Zcash protocol coin, by far, to operate
